== Introduction ==

RubyOSA is a bridge that connects Ruby to the AppleScript infrastructure. 
It automatically populates the API (classes, methods...) according to the 
target application's scriptable definition.

RubyOSA is an alternative to RubyAEOSA, and supposed to replace it.

RubyOSA is licensied under a BSD license, see the COPYRIGHT file for more 
information.

== Get started ==

$ ruby extconf.rb
$ make
$ sudo make install

== Support ==

Sample code is available in the `sample' sub-directory.

Feel free to send feedback to lsansonetti@apple.com.

When reporting a bug, please set the AEDebugSends and AEDebugReceives 
environment variables to 1 and attach the logs. 
